description: Supabase migrations, RLS, and Postgres function standards
globs: supabase/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# Migration Rules

- Create migrations only in `supabase/migrations/`.
- Use filename format `YYYYMMDDHHmmss_description.sql` (UTC).
- Write SQL in lowercase unless quoting requires otherwise.
- Include migration header comment with purpose, affected objects, and risks.
- Add explicit safety comments for destructive statements (`drop`, `alter`, `truncate`).
- New tables must enable RLS.
- After migration changes, run `yarn typegen` or `yarn typegen:remote`.

# RLS Rules

- Every API-exposed table must have RLS enabled.
- Each table must include restrictive policy `"require secure session"`:
  - `as restrictive for all`
  - `using ((select private.is_secure()))`
  - `with check ((select private.is_secure()))`
- For normal access control, split policies by operation (`select`, `insert`, `update`, `delete`).
- Use `auth.uid()` (often `(select auth.uid())`), never `current_user`.

# Function Rules

- Default to `security invoker`; use `security definer` only when required and documented.
- Always set `set search_path = '';`.
- Fully qualify object names in SQL/PLpgSQL.
- Reuse `public.trigger_set_updated_at`; do not create duplicate updated-at trigger functions.
